summaries.short: As an emboldened Crane looks to filter his poison through Gotham’s water system, Starfire - still plagued by visions - enlists Blackfire and Superboy’s help, and Gar finally tracks down Jason.
summaries.full: Emboldened by the success of his fear toxin, Crane moves to spread the poison through Gotham’s entire water system. Starfire’s persistent visions spur her to enlist Blackfire and Superboy’s help. Meanwhile, Gar finally tracks down Jason, who agrees to meet with Dick, and a savvy teenager pursues a position with the Titans.

summaries.short: After waking up on a mysterious train, Tim Drake teams with two familiar heroes to locate an elusive bridge back to the land of the living. Meanwhile, Rachel grapples with her own powers in a desperate attempt to resurrect Donna.
summaries.full: After waking up on a mysterious train headed to the underworld, Tim Drake runs into an unlikely hero. While pursued by dark forces, the duo teams with a familiar ally in search of an elusive bridge rumored to reach the land of the living. On Paradise Island, Rachel breaks every ancient law in a desperate attempt to resurrect her friend, Donna.

summaries.short: Gotham’s crime families meet to discuss the fear toxin’s hold on the city - only to be confronted by the mastermind himself. As Dick and Barbara consult the Oracle to preempt Crane’s next move, Starfire and Blackfire reach an understanding.
summaries.full: As the fear toxin wreaks havoc on Gotham, its mastermind presents the city’s most nefarious crime families with an irresistible proposition. Desperate to thwart Crane and Red Hood’s plans, Dick convinces Barbara to consult the supercomputer, Oracle. Then, Starfire and Blackfire put their differences aside to secure vital information from crime boss Valeska Nox.

summaries.short: Things go from bad to worse as the Titans are falsely blamed for poisoning the city, forcing them into a perilous position as they work to regain Gotham’s trust.
summaries.full: Gotham descends into chaos as the fear toxin infiltrates its water supply. But when Crane casts blame onto the Titans, making them public enemy number one, Dick must convince the team to make a perilous play for the city’s trust.

summaries.short: Dick and Barbara work to unmask the latest killer unleashed by Crane. When Kory and Gar bring her to the Tower, Blackfire forms an unexpected connection with a Titan.
summaries.full: When a new assassin descends on a reeling Gotham City, Dick and Barbara trace their highly lethal methods back to someone from their past. After Kory and Gar bring her back to the Tower, Blackfire finds a surprising ally in one of the Titans. Later, Crane and Red Hood begin the next phase of their plan.

summaries.short: While Crane sets his ultimate sights on Nightwing, Gar and Rachel investigate Red Hood’s place of rebirth, Donna and Tim reconnect in the real world, and Kory learns the truth about her past.
summaries.full: Relishing his reign of destruction, Crane sets the final piece of his plan into motion: ridding Gotham of Nightwing. Meanwhile, Gar and Rachel investigate the place of Red Hood’s rebirth, Donna and Tim reconnect, and Kory learns the truth about her family and powers.

summaries.short: In the aftermath of his fight with Nightwing, anti-heroes Red Hood and Jonathan Crane reteam for the first phase of their fearsome plan. Then, through a series of flashbacks, Red Hood’s origins are revealed.
summaries.full: After a battle with Nightwing, anti-heroes Red Hood and Jonathan Crane reteam for the first phase of a mission that shrouds Gotham in fear. Through a series of flashbacks retracing the end of Jason and Bruce Wayne’s partnership, Red Hood’s origins are finally revealed.
